p</gtr:grantCategory><gtr:grantReference>ES/G010358/1</gtr:grantReference><gtr:abstractText>&lt;p>The key aim of the proposed research is to publish it as a research monograph entitled 'A Critical Theory of Humanitarian Intervention'. &lt;/p>

&lt;p>The research explores the way in which reconceptualising security in terms of the Critical Theory focused on human development more broadly can improve upon the theoretical and practical limitations of the solidarist theorising on the subject of humanitarian intervention. &lt;/p>

&lt;p>These limitations stem from its unsustainable approach to analysing supreme humanitarian emergencies, where the focus is on intervening to manage these emergencies when they are already in full flight rather than preventing the emergence of conditions out of which they arise in the first place.&lt;/p>

&lt;p>In an attempt to move beyond these limitations, in the research it is synthesised between the elements of Critical Theory (ie reflexive theorising, particular understanding of change and emancipation) and political practice to argue two things: first, that theories of humanitarian intervention need to focus on the logically prior question of how best to prevent the outbreak of supreme humanitarian emergencies rather than on how best to manage such outbreaks; and second, they need to encourage a conception of security which gives at least equal weight to questions of development. &lt;br />&lt;/p></gtr:abstractText><gtr:fund><gtr:end>2011-12-31</gtr:end><gtr:funder url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/organisation/924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE"><gtr:id>924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE</gtr:id><gtr:name>ESRC</gtr:name></gtr:funder><gtr:start>2008-10-01</gtr:start><gtr:type>INCOME_ACTUAL</gtr:type><gtr:valuePounds>81178</gtr:valuePounds></gtr:fund><gtr:output><gtr:artisticAndCreativeProductOutputs/><gtr:collaborationOutputs/><gtr:disseminationOutputs/><gtr:exploitationOutputs/><gtr:furtherFundingOutputs/><gtr:impactSummaryOutputs/><gtr:intellectualPropertyOutputs/><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications><gtr:publication><gtr:id>6DA39448-2670-43A2-A2DB-24F9AA864B80</gtr:id><gtr:title>A Critical Humanitarian Intervention Approach</gtr:title><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/dcbed65d2e9b4afcef3b1efcc88764c0"><gtr:id>dcbed65d2e9b4afcef3b1efcc88764c0</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Butler Karina Zofia</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2011-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:isbn>9780230216563</gtr:isbn><gtr:outcomeId>i_54062824533b8fd4a6</gtr:outcomeId></gtr:publication></gtr:publications><gtr:identifiers><gtr:identifier type="RCUK">ES/G010358/1</gtr